data.title: The Best Rappers From Queens, NYC
data.meta_description: Over 1K music fans have voted on the 50+ Best Rappers From Queens, NYC. Current Top 3: Nas, Mobb Deep, A Tribe Called Quest

Voting Rules

Only famous rappers who were born in or started their careers in Queens, New York.

From new artists to some of the greatest hip hop artists of all time, here are the best rappers from Queens, New York. Including both solo artists, like 50 Cent and Nicki Minaj, and hip hop groups, like Run-DMC and G-Unit, this list of the most popular Queens rappers features rap artists who were born or raised in the NYC borough. Known for their style of East Coast hip hop, famous Queens rappers also include LL Cool J, A Tribe Called Quest, Ja Rule, and Waka Flocka Flame. Who are the top Queens rappers of all-time?

Vote up the best hip hop artists from Queens reppin' New York City's largest borough.

Most divisive: Waka Flocka Flame

Over 1.5K Ranker voters have come together to rank this list of The Best Rappers From Queens, NYC

Hailing from the Queensbridge Houses, this lyrical genius has been a prominent figure in hip-hop since his groundbreaking 1994 debut album, which showcased his vivid storytelling and intricate wordplay. With a career spanning over two decades, he's built an extensive discography that has solidified his status as one of the greatest MCs of all time, while also inspiring countless artists both in and outside of the borough.

This iconic duo, consisting of Prodigy and Havoc, emerged from the Queensbridge projects with their dark and gritty tales of street life, painting vivid pictures through their haunting beats and menacing rhymes. Their signature sound played a pivotal role in shaping East Coast hip-hop during the '90s, and they continue to be celebrated for their raw lyricism and unapologetic portrayal of life in New York City's toughest neighborhoods.

Comprised of Q-Tip, Phife Dawg, Ali Shaheed Muhammad, and Jarobi White, this influential group helped pioneer alternative hip-hop with their eclectic blend of jazz-infused beats and socially conscious lyrics. Hailing from St. Albans in Queens, they left an indelible mark on the hip-hop landscape with their innovative approach to music-making and thought-provoking subject matter that transcended genre boundaries.

Born in South Jamaica, this multi-talented artist rose to fame with his hard-hitting rhymes about surviving street life and his captivating storytelling ability. Through a combination of business savvy, relentless work ethic, and undeniable charisma, he's become a global superstar and one of the most successful figures in hip-hop history, all while staying true to his Queens roots.

Consisting of Joseph "Run" Simmons, Darryl "D.M.C." McDaniels, and Jason "Jam Master Jay" Mizell, this groundbreaking trio from Hollis changed the face of hip-hop with their fusion of rock-infused beats and innovative fashion sense. Their undeniable impact on both music and popular culture has solidified them as trailblazers who paved the way for countless acts that followed in their footsteps.

Widely regarded as one of the greatest lyricists of all time, this Corona-born pioneer is known for his complex rhyme schemes and gritty street narratives that laid the foundation for future generations of MCs. His rapid-fire delivery and vivid storytelling have earned him a place among the rap elite, with countless artists citing him as a major influence on their own careers.
